trump <- getPage('hillaryclinton', token = token, n = 5)

Analyzing the data using quanteda

From this, we can create a quanteda corpus:

# creating corpus object
fbdata <- rbind(obama, trump)
fbcorpus <- corpus(fbdata$message, docvars = fbdata[, -which(names(fbdata)=="message")])
summary(fbcorpus)

Authenticate using the Twitter tokens from https://apps.twitter.com

## data for authentication
## get your keys at apps.twitter.com
require(twitteR)
key <- "xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
cons_secret <- "xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
token <- "xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
access_secret <- "xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
# authorize the Twitter access
setup_twitter_oauth(key, cons_secret, token, access_secret)

Download Tweets

Get the most recent Tweets from President-Elect Donald J. Trump, and create from this a quanteda corpus object:

tw <- userTimeline("realDonaldTrump", n = 3200, includeRts = TRUE)
twCorpus <- corpus(twListToDF(tw), textField = "text")
head(texts(twCorpus))

Plot some word clouds

## creating corpus and dfm objects, and word cloud
twDfm <- dfm(twCorpus, 
             ignoredFeatures = c("amp", "rt", "https", "t.co", "will", 
                                 "@realdonaldtrump", stopwords("english")))
## Creating a dfm from a corpus ...

plot(twDfm, min.freq = 20, random.order = FALSE)

We can select just hashtags, using selectFeatures():

## analyze just hashtags
twDfmHT <- selectFeatures(twDfm, "#*")
## kept 273 features, from 1 supplied (glob) feature types
plot(twDfmHT, min.freq = 5, random.order = FALSE)
## Warning in wordcloud::wordcloud(features(x), colSums(x), ...):
## #makeamericagreatagain could not be fit on page. It will not be plotted.

We can select just usernames, using selectFeatures():

## analyze just usernames
plot(selectFeatures(twDfm, "@*"), min.freq = 5, random.order = FALSE)
## kept 587 features, from 1 supplied (glob) feature types

We can analyze by candidate:

## analyze by candidate
require(magrittr)
## Loading required package: magrittr
twHCCorpus <- userTimeline("HillaryClinton", n = 3200, includeRts = TRUE) %>%
                  twListToDF %>% 
                      corpus(textField = "text")

Now we can add the two corpus objects together, and create a dfm that is segmented by username:

candDfm <- dfm(twCorpus + twHCCorpus, 
               groups = "screenName",
               ignoredFeatures = c("amp", "rt", "https", "t.co", "will", "@tedcruz",
                                   "@realdonaldtrump", stopwords("english")))
